<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-443-905  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 443 905.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Sept 10 1990 v12 n37 p114(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Corporate Voice provides in-depth style replication: packagestandardizes corporate writing style. (Software Review)(Scandinavian PC Systems' Corporate Voice) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Irvin, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Scandinavian PC Systems Inc's $119.95 Corporate Voice is a veryeffective program for replicating a given style of writing.andP;  Thepremise of Corporate Voice is that an organization can giveCorporate Voice a sample of writing that represents the style itwould like all of its writing to mimic.andP;  Corporate Voice will thencompare any other sample of writing with the standard model andpoint out the disparities.andP;  The model document needs to be ratherlong, at least 20,000 words, but Corporate Voice requires an indepth model to provide in depth critiquing of other writing.andO;Overall, the program does a very thorough job of analyzingwriting, and large organizations that want to standardize thequality of their writing would do well to purchase this program.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Scandinavian PC Systems Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Corporate Voice 1.0 (Computer program).andO;Topic:     EvaluationGrammar CritiquingWriting SkillsStyle CritiquingSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>